 In AIGs UK buildings, the target is to reduce emissions by 20% below the 2010 baseline level by 2020 This is in compliance with the UKs Carbon Reduction Commitment The target for AIGs New York City buildings is to reduce emissions by 30% below the 2011 baseline level by 2023 The New York City target was adopted as part of AIGs participation in the New York City Mayors Carbon Challenge (a commitment to track carbon emissions annually and create an emissions reduction strategy for AIGs New York City buildings)  

AIG is committed to implementing practices that reduce the environmental impact of our business Efforts include encouraging the companys suppliers to improve the sustainability of products and services, increasing the efficiencies of internal company operations and physical assets under the companys control, and reducing energy usage Multiple projects were completed during the reporting year across our Global Operations upgrading building infrastructure at AIG's owned and leased office operations driving energy efficiency, to include:

	Lighting upgrades across multiple facilities to LED and/or more efficient T8;
	Replacement / Upgrade of Cooling tower at 22M square foot owned campus; 
	Consolidation and replacement of legacy (data center / computer) servers to new highly efficient blade servers  

Additionally, AIG has invested more than $500 million over the past three years to upgrade our worldwide offices, including the use of high efficiency lighting, sustainably manufactured products, and energy-efficient mechanical infrastructure  Globally, AIG has launched a strategy to reduce office footprints through consolidation, densification, and work from home strategies which will result in future long term reductions to our overall carbon emissions
